/>This section will teach you about the importance of authentic language and interaction as you meet twice a week with your Pathway student.<strong><br /></strong><br /><a href="x41884.xml"><strong>Corrective Feedback</strong></a><br />Should you correct every mistake your partner makes? Should you just let them talk, correcting no mistakes? How do you find an appropriate balance between these two extremes? This lesson will help you understand where the balance is and how to find it.<strong><br /><br /></strong><a href="x41887.xml"><strong>Assessing Your Partner</strong></a><br />Twice a semester, you will receive an email requesting that you submit an evaluation based on the student's progress with their English speaking skills. This section will teach you how to appropriately assess the student's progress and what kinds of issues you should report.<strong><br /><br /></strong><a href="x41885.xml"><strong>Building Appropriate Relationships</strong></a><br />As you work with your Pathway student, you will develop close bonds of friendship. However, it is important to make sure that these relationships are appropriate and do not cross any boundaries. In this section, you will learn about what those boundaries are and how to make sure you are staying within them.<br /><br /><br /></p>
